## 4. Auto Portfolio Opt-In/Opt-Out

Users must have full control over whether they participate in AI-managed auto-recommendations. The auto portfolio is an **entirely optional feature**.

### Opt-In/Opt-Out Mechanics

- **Default state:** Auto portfolio is **off by default**. Users must explicitly opt in during onboarding or later through settings.
- **Opt-in process:**
  - User navigates to the Auto Portfolio section
  - Presented with an explanation of how auto-recommendations work, including risk disclosures
  - Must accept the liability clause (Section 2) specific to auto-recommendations
  - Selects a risk tolerance profile (conservative, moderate, aggressive) to calibrate recommendations
  - Confirms opt-in
- **Opt-out process:**
  - Users can disable auto-recommendations at any time from Settings > Portfolio Preferences
  - Upon opting out, a confirmation prompt asks if they want to:
    - Keep existing AI-recommended holdings as-is (manual management going forward)
    - Receive a one-time summary of current AI-managed positions for manual review
  - No penalty, lock-in period, or loss of access to other features
- **Granular controls:** Users may opt in to specific aspects of the auto portfolio (e.g., receive recommendations but require manual execution, or auto-execute only for certain asset classes or dollar thresholds).

### Feature Access When Opted Out

Users who opt out retain full access to:
- Manual portfolio tracking and management
- Financial decision-making tools (Section 7)
- Market data, news, and educational resources
- Budgeting and savings features
- All non-recommendation functionality

