## 6. Cross-Platform Compatibility

The application must deliver a seamless, consistent experience across all major platforms and devices.

### Supported Platforms

- **Mobile - iOS:** Native or hybrid app supporting iPhone and iPad, targeting iOS 15+.
- **Mobile - Android:** Native or hybrid app supporting phones and tablets, targeting Android 10+.
- **Web - Desktop:** Responsive web application supporting Chrome, Firefox, Safari, and Edge (latest 2 versions).
- **Web - Mobile:** Fully responsive mobile web experience for users who prefer browser access over installing an app.

### Technical Approach

- **Responsive design:** The UI must adapt fluidly across screen sizes from 320px (small phones) to 2560px+ (ultrawide monitors).
- **Framework consideration:** Evaluate cross-platform frameworks (React Native, Flutter) to maximize code reuse between mobile and web while maintaining native performance.
- **Progressive Web App (PWA):** Consider implementing PWA capabilities for the web version to support offline access, push notifications, and home screen installation on mobile browsers.
- **API-first architecture:** Build a unified backend API that serves all client platforms consistently, ensuring data and feature parity across devices.

### Platform-Specific Considerations

- **Mobile:**
  - Biometric authentication (Face ID, Touch ID, fingerprint) for login and trade confirmations
  - Push notifications for recommendation alerts, trade confirmations, and market events
  - Optimized touch targets and gestures for trade confirmation flows
  - Offline mode for portfolio viewing and budgeting tools (syncs when reconnected)
  - Widget support (iOS widgets, Android widgets) for quick portfolio glance
- **Web:**
  - Keyboard shortcuts for power users
  - Multi-tab/multi-window support for monitoring multiple stocks
  - Browser notification support
  - Export and print functionality for reports and tax documents

### Performance Standards

- App load time under 3 seconds on 4G connections
- Smooth 60fps animations and transitions
- Real-time or near-real-time data updates for stock prices and portfolio values
- Accessibility compliance (WCAG 2.1 AA) across all platforms

